d: JWT validation, room joining, event handling. Issues: Events are emitted outs
ide of database transactions (but the service doesn\'t use transactions for mess
age save, so it\'s consistent). The `message:receive` event uses `sender_id` fro
m message entity but the DTO says it can be null for system messages. However, `
message:send` only handles user messages, system messages are created via `match
:created` event.\n\n2. `im.service.ts` - Issues found:\n   - `getMessages` pagin
ation `next_cursor` logic is buggy: It returns `messages[0].sequence_id` after r
eversing, but `messages[0]` is the oldest message in the returned set (because o
f reverse()). For cursor pagination descending, the next cursor should be the mi
nimum sequence_id in the returned set (i.e., `messages[messages.length-1].sequen
ce_id` after reverse, or `results[results.length-1].sequence_id` before reverse)
. Currently it returns the oldest message\'s sequence_id which will cause pagina
tion to skip messages.\n   - Raw SQL in `getConversations` uses `?` placeholder 
with `IN (?)` which may not work correctly with MySQL when passing an array. Typ
eORM\'s query with `IN (?)` and `[conversationIds]` may or may not expand the ar
ray properly depending on the driver version. This is a potential bug.\n   - `se
ndMessage` doesn\'t use a database transaction. The spec says "事务边界" should 
be checked for DB modifications.\n   - `createSystemMessage` sets `sender_id: nu
ll` but the `ReadReceiptDto` uses `last_message_id` - what if the last message i
s a system message with null sender_id? The read receipt should still work.\n   
- `markAsRead` doesn\'t validate that `last_message_id` actually exists in the c
onversation.\n   - The `getConversations` method uses `cp.updated_at` for cursor
pagination, but there\'s no index on `updated_at` mentioned.\n\n3. `im.controlle
r.ts` - Good: Uses guards, validates query params. Issue: `getMessages` endpoint
doesn\'t have `@Query(\'conversation_id\')` validated as required at the decorat
or level - it just returns a custom error response. Not a big issue.\n\n4. Migra
tion file: `AlterMessagesSenderIdNullable20250425000000` - Good, handles nullabl
e sender_id for system messages. But the `down` method adds back the FK constrai
nt without checking if it exists. Also, if the original table was created with a
different FK name, this could fail.\n\n5. Tests: Backend tests cover the main pa
ths. However, matching service tests don\'t seem to test the `match:created` eve
nt emission or the system message creation.\n\n**Mobile (Flutter):**\n1. `chat_p
age.dart` - Good use of design tokens, Semantics with identifiers for Maestro. U
ses `onTapDown` correctly. One issue: When messages are empty, it shows the syst
em message "你们已匹配成功，开始聊天吧" but this is hardcoded and may not be app
ropriate if the conversation has no messages for other reasons (e.g., user delet
ed messages). Not a major issue.\n\n2. `match_list_page.dart` - Good implementat
ion. Uses `SwConversationListItem`. Has empty state. `_formatTime` has a bug: wh
en `diff.inHours > 0` it returns `${time.hour}:${time.minute}` but this shows th
e message time, not the elapsed time. Wait, let me re-read... Actually it return
s the time of day (like "14:30"), which is standard for chat apps. That\'s fine.
\n\n3. `im_bloc.dart` - Issues:\n   - `_onMessageReceived` emits `ImMessageSent`
when a message is received. This is semantically incorrect - should emit somethi
ng like `ImMessageReceived` or reuse `ImMessagesLoaded`. But looking at the stat
es, `ImMessageSent` is used both for "message sent by me acked" and "message rec
eived from other". This is confusing but functionally works because the UI just 
needs the message list.\n   - `_onLoadMessages` inserts new messages at index 0 
(`_messages.insertAll(0, result.items)`) but the API returns messages in ascendi
ng order. If the bloc already has messages and loads more (pagination), insertin
g at 0 would put older messages at the beginning, which is correct for a bottom-
up list. However, the initial load clears `_messages` first. This seems okay.\n 
 - `_onReadReceipt` has a bug: It iterates through all messages and marks self m
essages as read up to `lastReadMessageId`. But if `lastReadMessageId` is not in 
the list, it marks ALL self messages as read, even those sent after the user sup
posedly read. This could incorrectly mark future messages as read. Actually the 
logic says `lastReadIndex == -1 || i <= lastReadIndex`. If `lastReadIndex == -1`
, it marks ALL self messages as read. This is a bug - if the receipt references 
a message not loaded yet, it shouldn\'t mark all loaded messages as read. Wait, 
but if `lastReadMessageId` refers to a message that the sender hasn\'t loaded ye
t (e.g., sender scrolled up and hasn\'t loaded newer messages), marking all curr
ently visible self messages as read would be wrong if there are newer unread mes
sages not in the list. However, since the list is ordered chronologically and th
e read receipt typically refers to the latest message, and if the sender has all
messages loaded (which they likely do if they just sent them), this might be oka
y in practice. But it\'s still a potential bug.\n   - The `ImBloc` creates a new
